The Americans have a new "smart weapon"
The U.S. military has sent a new "smart" weapon to Afghanistan, known only by the code name XM-25.
The generals believe that this new automatic rifle will influence the conflict there with the Taliban and "change the game" in their favor.
The new weapon is like a super-accurate cannon
Its projectiles are laser-guided with an accuracy of a few meters.
The special 25 mm calibre ammunition developed for this rifle and containing a highly destructive explosive, actually works like small grenades.
The munitions can be programmed to explode not only when they hit the target but also at any point along their ballistic trajectory.
So it can be used against an enemy who is hiding behind an obstacle, a wall or a ditch.
He's also not protected from above, and when a deadly rain of steel splinters falls on him, it can knock him out of action as well.
According to Richard Audette who took part in the development of the XM-25, the new rifle is the first infantry weapon to use "intelligent" technology.
"The soldier basically uses it in such a way that he finds the target, sends a laser beam to it that determines the distance, thus obtaining a precise aiming point, according to which he corrects his aiming point and presses the trigger.
"Let's say you aimed at 543 yards".
