Is the Splatter film a fake movie?
Director Nicolas Winding Refn explores the boundaries of the ancient genre with his film, "Walhalla Rising", an epic of the warrior.
What kind of audience did Danish director Nicolas Winding Refn have in mind when he made Walhalla Rising?
A one-eyed Viking warrior (Mads Mikkelsen) is captured; he frees himself from his executioner and, with almost supernatural strength, eliminates his opponents one by one. This seems ideal for young male spectators looking for bloody action, precisely because our hero uses brutal assassination methods. When he is in a bad mood, he rips out the intestines of his enemies without waiting for them to be dead.
