"Pakistan has to hire personnel with strict religious beliefs to protect nuclear facilities; given the decline in educational and cultural levels, extremist organizations have more opportunities to recruit people who work in nuclear or missile programs", Russian Foreign Ministry expert Yuri Korolev said during a meeting with his US counterparts.
The newest of the leaked documentation from Julian Assange's website is the ever-decreasing cooperation between the United States and Pakistan in the field of nuclear proliferation and the high degree of Pakistani nuclear weapons production.
A May embassy dispatch, which called communication with Pakistan "frustrating", said: "Transparency is frequently lacking; offers of help go unanswered or are eliminated".
In another message, Peter Lavoy, National Intelligence Officer for South Asia, notes that "despite the economic disaster, Pakistan is developing nuclear weapons at a faster rate than any other country in the world".
