China maintains greenhouse gas reduction targets
The country's representative at COP16 said that his country has made enormous efforts to reduce its carbon footprint and said that it maintains its pledge to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45 percent by 2020.
China is sticking to its pledge to cut its greenhouse gas emissions by 40 to 45 percent by 2020, said Su Wei, China's representative to COP16.
